dc_title_s: Turtle Nesting Sites on the Eastern Coast of Kenya, 2006
dc_description_s: This point shapefile contains locations of turtle nesting and breeding sites on the eastern coast of Kenya. This data was used in Map 6.4 and Map 6.5 in Nature's Benefits in Kenya: An Atlas of Ecosystems and Human Well-Being. United Nations Development Programme (Kenya), Kenya Marine and Fisheries Research Institute and Geological Survey of Denmark . (2006). Turtle Nesting Sites on the Eastern Coast of Kenya, 2006. World Resources Institute. KMFRI and GSD. Available at: http://purl.stanford.edu/rp968zc9902 The full report is available at http://www.geus.dk/program-areas/nature-environment/international/reports/kensea/kensea_rapport.pdf. Data set is not for use in litigation. While efforts have been made to ensure that these data are accurate and reliable within the state of the art, WRI, cannot assume liability for any damages, or misrepresentations, caused by any inaccuracies in the data, or as a result of the data to be used on a particular system.
